@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Webly" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Webly runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, click on an octagonal shaped tile and the game will
randomly create a link between it and another tile that is located
nearby. If a link was already present between both tiles, that link
will change its colour...

  The goal is to make all the links that can be made between tiles
of a game board, while avoiding as much as possible that some links
change colour. An indicator, shown at the right of the game board,
displays the number of links that have been made against the number
of links that have to be made.

  You can restart a game board anytime by clicking on the 'Replay'
button. However, note that the number of moves you make on a game
board accumulates until you complete it...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

